<% content_for :title, "Pregame template — Rule 0 the bracket way" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "A copy-pasteable pregame template that replaces 'my deck is a 7' with the actual features that determine a Commander game: bracket, Game Changers, mass land denial, extra turns, two-card combos, win conditions, expected turn." %>
<% site_origin = "#{request.protocol}#{request.host_with_port}" %>
<% content_for :jsonld_extra, jsonld_tag(
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Ideal Magic", "item": "#{site_origin}/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Commander Brackets", "item": "#{site_origin}#{brackets_path}" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Pregame template" }
  ]
) %>

<article class="space-y-8">
  <header class="space-y-3">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-emerald-300">Bracket reference · Pregame template</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white sm:text-4xl">A pregame template that actually says something</h1>
    <p class="max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-zinc-300">
      "My deck is a 7" doesn't tell anyone whether you're winning with combat, a protected combo, prison pieces, or fast mana. The bracket-aware pregame template names the features that actually decide the game.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="space-y-3">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Template</h2>
    <pre class="overflow-x-auto rounded border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950 p-4 font-mono text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-100">This is a Bracket [X] deck.
It is trying to win by:
  [combat / value engine / aristocrats / spellslinger / combo / commander damage / stax / reanimator / etc.]
It has:
  [N] Game Changers
  [yes/no] fast mana
  [yes/no] free interaction
  [yes/no] tutors for win pieces
  [yes/no] two-card infinites or lockouts
  [yes/no] extra-turn chaining
  [yes/no] mass land denial
It usually threatens to win around turn:
  [N]
The play experience is:
  [theme showcase / casual battlecruiser / tuned synergy / high-power / cEDH]</pre>
  </section>

  <section class="grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <article class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">Bracket 3 Voja</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">"This is Bracket 3 Voja. It has 2 Game Changers, no mass land denial, no chained extra turns, and no early deterministic two-card combo. It can produce a huge combat turn after building a board, usually around turn six or later. It is tuned creature-combat snowball, not cEDH."</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">Bracket 2 Ghyrson Starn</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">"This is Bracket 2 Ghyrson Starn. Zero Game Changers, no MLD, no extra-turn chaining, no two-card win. It pings the table for damage with damage-doublers. It usually closes a winning game around turn nine. The play experience is casual battlecruiser."</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">Bracket 1 Weatherlight Crew</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">"This is Bracket 1 Weatherlight crew. Theme deck — every creature is a named Weatherlight character. No Game Changers, no MLD, no extra turns, no combos. Wins are slow and incidental. Asking the pod for one Rule 0 exception so I can run [thematic card]."</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">Bracket 4 Pantlaza</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">"This is Bracket 4 Pantlaza. 5 Game Changers including Mana Vault, Vampiric Tutor, and Smothering Tithe. Fast mana, free interaction, no MLD, no extra-turn chaining, no two-card immediate-win combo. Threatens lethal commander damage around turn five. Not cEDH-tuned."</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">Bracket 5 Thoracle Tymna/Kraum</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-300">"This is Bracket 5 cEDH Tymna/Kraum. Standard Thoracle/Consultation finish, Force of Will, Force of Negation, Fierce Guardianship, full fast-mana suite. Wins on any turn. Playing the standard cEDH metagame."</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/40 p-6 text-sm text-zinc-300">
    <p class="font-medium text-white">Pod prompt</p>
    <p class="mt-2">When seating a pod, agree on the floor first: "We're playing a Bracket 3 game. Anyone bringing a deck higher than that, swap or be honest." Brackets work when they're agreed before hands are kept.</p>
  </section>
</article>
